\section{Methodology}

\subsection{Study Area and Data}

The study utilizes LiDAR point cloud data from SVAMITVA for two villages in Gujarat:
\begin{longtable}{lrrrr}
	\toprule
	\textbf{Village} & \textbf{District} & \textbf{Points} & \textbf{Density (pts/m2)} & \textbf{Format} \\
	\midrule
	DEVDI            & Ahmedabad         & 64,622,538      & 65.07                     & LAS             \\
	KHAPRETA         & Sabar Kantha      & 163,743,261     & 245.28                    & LAZ             \\
	\bottomrule
\end{longtable}

Both datasets lack pre-existing ground classification and have zero intensity variation (a known characteristic of SVAMITVA Phase 1 data). The coordinate reference system is EPSG:32643 (UTM Zone 43N).

\subsection{System Architecture}

The pipeline is implemented as a six-stage Python workflow with modular design:

\bigskip

