\section{Implementation}

\subsection{Software Stack}

\begin{longtable}{lll}
	\toprule
	\textbf{Component}      & \textbf{Technology}            & \textbf{Purpose}                      \\
	\midrule
	Point Cloud I/O         & laspy, PDAL                    & LAS/LAZ reading and filtering         \\
	Ground Classification   & PDAL SMRF/CSF, scikit-learn RF & Terrain surface identification        \\
	Deep Learning           & PyTorch, PointNet              & Optional advanced classification      \\
	Interpolation           & SciPy IDW, scipy.ndimage       & DTM raster generation                 \\
	Raster Processing       & rasterio, rio-cogeo, GDAL      & COG creation and manipulation         \\
	Hydrological Modelling  & pysheds                        & Flow analysis and stream extraction   \\
	Waterlogging Prediction & XGBoost                        & ML-based risk mapping                 \\
	Network Optimization    & NetworkX (MST)                 & Drainage network design               \\
	Vector GIS              & GeoPandas, Shapely, Fiona      & GPKG creation                         \\
	Visualization           & matplotlib, rich               & Terminal output formatting            \\
	Configuration           & PyYAML                         & Parameter management                  \\
	Logging                 & loguru                         & Structured logging and error tracking \\
	\bottomrule
\end{longtable}

All dependencies are specified in \texttt{requirements.txt} for environment reproducibility.

\subsection{Directory Structure}

\begin{verbatim}
dtm-drainage-ai/
|-- config/
|   |-- config.yaml              # All tunable parameters
|-- src/
|   |-- preprocessing/
|   |   |-- point_cloud_loader.py
|   |   |-- ground_classifier.py
|   |-- dtm/
|   |   |-- dtm_generator.py
|   |   |-- terrain_analysis.py
|   |-- hydrology/
|   |   |-- flow_analysis.py
|   |   |-- waterlogging_predictor.py
|   |   |-- drainage_network.py
|   |-- ml/
|   |   |-- pointnet_classifier.py
|   |-- evaluation/
|   |-- pipelines/
|   |   |-- full_pipeline.py
|-- data/
|-- logs/
\end{verbatim}

\subsection{Configuration Management}

All pipeline parameters are managed via \texttt{config.yaml}:

\begin{verbatim}
dtm:
  resolution: 0.5
  interpolation:
    method: "idw"
    idw_power: 2
    idw_radius: 5.0
  smoothing:
    sigma: 1.0

waterlogging:
  model: "xgboost"
  threshold: 0.45
  xgboost:
    n_estimators: 500
    max_depth: 7
    learning_rate: 0.05

drainage:
  design_return_period: 10
  rainfall_intensity: 50
  runoff_coefficient: 0.65
  manning_n: 0.025
  cost_per_metre_channel: 800
\end{verbatim}

This design enables non-technical users to modify parameters without code changes.

\subsection{Installation (pip-based)}

The pipeline uses pure pip installation without conda dependency:

\begin{enumerate}
	\item Create virtual environment:
	      \begin{verbatim}
python -m venv dtm-env
dtm-env\Scripts\activate
    \end{verbatim}

	\item Install PDAL (via OSGeo4W or standalone binaries):
	      \begin{verbatim}
# Download from https://pdal.io/en/latest/download.html
# OR use QGIS bundled PDAL (default path configured)
    \end{verbatim}

	\item Install Python dependencies:
	      \begin{verbatim}
pip install -r requirements.txt
    \end{verbatim}

	\item (Optional) GPU support for PointNet:
	      \begin{verbatim}
pip install torch torchvision --index-url \
  https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu121
    \end{verbatim}

	\item Set QGIS path (Windows):
	      \begin{verbatim}
# The pipeline auto-detects QGIS bundeled PDAL at:
# C:\Program Files\QGIS 3.40.15\bin\pdal.exe
# Update _QGIS_BIN in ground_classifier.py if needed
    \end{verbatim}
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{Command-Line Interface}

The pipeline provides a user-friendly CLI:

\begin{verbatim}
python run_pipeline.py --input data/input/DEVDI_511671.las
python run_pipeline.py --input <file> --output data/output/devdi
python run_pipeline.py --batch
python run_pipeline.py --input <file> --no-ml
python run_pipeline.py --input <file> --stream-threshold 500
\end{verbatim}

Stage selection is supported: \texttt{--stages 3,4,5} runs only hydrology onwards.

