\bigskip

\subsection{PointNet (Optional Deep Learning)}

An optional PointNet model is provided for advanced ground classification:

\begin{itemize}
	\item Input: 1024-point patches (voxel-sampled);
	\item T-Net: Input alignment transformation;
	\item MLP: Shared FC layers (64, 128, 1024);
	\item Max pooling: Global feature aggregation;
	\item Output: Per-point binary classification.
\end{itemize}

PointNet requires GPU acceleration and is disabled by default to ensure CPU compatibility.

\subsection{Deployment Guidelines}

The pipeline is designed for deployment in resource-constrained environments:

\begin{enumerate}
	\item \textbf{Environment}: Python 3.10+ virtual environment, PDAL, GDAL;
	\item \textbf{Hardware}: 16 GB RAM minimum, 32 GB recommended; SSD for temp files;
	\item \textbf{Execution}: Single-machine for $<$ 100M points; distributed tiling for larger;
	\item \textbf{Logging}: Structured JSON logs with error tracking for debugging;
	\item \textbf{Output Validation}: Automated statistics computation and quality flags.
\end{enumerate}

Future deployment may leverage cloud processing (AWS Lambda, Google Cloud Functions) for burst capacity during large village batch processing.

