\section{Accuracy Metrics and Validation}

\subsection{Ground Classification Metrics}

Validation used held-out test points with manually verified labels:

\begin{longtable}{lrrr}
	\toprule
	\textbf{Metric} & \textbf{SMRF Only} & \textbf{SMRF + RF} \\
	\midrule
	Precision       & 0.71               & 0.84               \\
	Recall          & 0.89               & 0.87               \\
	F1-Score        & 0.79               & 0.85               \\
	Kappa           & 0.58               & 0.71               \\
	\bottomrule
\end{longtable}

Random Forest refinement improves overall accuracy by 6 percentage points, primarily by reducing false positives in built-up areas.

\subsection{DTM Accuracy}

DTM accuracy was evaluated against surveyed ground control points:

\begin{longtable}{lrr}
	\toprule
	\textbf{Metric} & \textbf{DEVDI} & \textbf{KHAPRETA} \\
	\midrule
	RMSE            & 0.34 m         & 0.52 m            \\
	MAE             & 0.21 m         & 0.38 m            \\
	Bias            & -0.05 m        & +0.12 m           \\
	Max Error       & 1.12 m         & 1.87 m            \\
	\bottomrule
\end{longtable}

The KHAPRETA dataset shows higher error due to steeper terrain (greater interpolation uncertainty).

\subsection{Waterlogging Model}

\begin{longtable}{lrr}
	\toprule
	\textbf{Metric}          & \textbf{Value}  \\
	\midrule
	ROC-AUC (5-fold CV)      & 0.82 $\pm$ 0.04 \\
	Average Precision        & 0.79            \\
	Recall at 45\% threshold & 0.75            \\
	False Positive Rate      & 0.18            \\
	\bottomrule
\end{longtable}

The model demonstrates good discrimination ability but warrants validation against actual flood event data when available.

\subsection{Drainage Network}

\begin{longtable}{lrr}
	\toprule
	\textbf{Metric}          & \textbf{Value}    \\
	\midrule
	Hydraulic Capacity Check & All segments pass \\
	Velocity (min/max)       & 0.45 / 1.78 m/s   \\
	Freeboard Compliance     & 100\%             \\
	Cost per metre (avg)     & Rs. 8,000/m       \\
	Total Project Cost       & Rs. 4.06 crores   \\
	\bottomrule
\end{longtable}

All designed channels meet the minimum velocity (self-cleaning, 0.3 m/s) and maximum velocity (erosion limit, 2.0 m/s) constraints.

