\section{Conclusion and Future Work}

\subsection{Summary}

This research presents a complete AI/ML-driven pipeline for DTM generation and drainage network design from drone point cloud data. The key contributions are:

\begin{enumerate}
	\item \textbf{Three-stage ground classification} combining SMRF, CSF, and Random Forest refinement---achieving F1 = 0.85 on test data;
	\item \textbf{Automated DTM generation} at 0.5 m resolution with COG export (RMSE = 0.34 m);
	\item \textbf{Hydrological analysis} with pysheds enabling flow path delineation and catchment mapping;
	\item \textbf{XGBoost waterlogging predictor} trained on terrain features (ROC-AUC = 0.82);
	\item \textbf{MST-optimized drainage network} with Manning's equation sizing and cost estimation (Rs. 4.06 crores for DEVDI);
	\item \textbf{OGC-compliant outputs} (COG, GPKG, LAS 1.4) for direct GIS integration.
\end{enumerate}

The pipeline is operational, reproducible, and configurable via YAML. It successfully processes point clouds from two Gujarat villages, demonstrating scalability to larger datasets.

